Defendant Mark K Nickel in court with attorney Anthony D Cotton.  Andrea M Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS 2 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT;
  -  1 YEAR 2 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION: 3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended; 
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia. 
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription; 
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed. 
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions; 
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling;  
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done. 
*Perform 120 Hours Community Service. 

DAY REPORT CENTER: 120 Days, consecutive to condition time.

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be refunded to poster);

CONDITION TIME: 180 Days, non working hours.  Last 120 days stayed for day report. Commencing 3/5/18. Defendant currently at the Huber Facility and is to report back today 3/5/18 at the previously scheduled time set by Huber Facility.   

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
